President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday felicitated with former President Olusegun Obasanjo on his 83rd birthday, holding today. Buhari, in a statement by his spokesman, Femi Adesina, congratulated Obasanjo for a life of courage, dedication and service to Nigeria, Africa, and humanity in general. He acknowledged that Obasanjo’s commitment to Nigerian nationhood remained outstanding and commendable. Buhari also stressed the former president’s sacrifices for the continent, including standing up for democracy in many countries. Buhari prayed the Almighty God to grant the ex-president longer life, good health and strength to keep serving the nation and the continent.  Obasanjo’s commitment to Nigeria commendable — Buhari The Oracle from Otta has spoken Buhari felicitates with Obasanjo at 82, salutes his commitment to Nigeria